          .hex #f2a900
        .color
          .sample(class='light-blue')
          .name Light Blue
          .hex #0077c8
        .color
          .sample(class='green')
          .name Green
          .hex #2c5234
        .color
          .sample(class='tan')
          .name Tan
          .hex #d18644

  .guide
    .content
      h2 Production
      p The New York flag has an unusual proportion of 1:2. If the flag has a hoist of 3 feet, its fly should be 6 feet.
      p If resized, it must maintain these proportions.
    .visual
      img(src='/assets/images/flag-new-york-dimensions.svg')

  .guide
    .content
      h2 Previous iteration
      p The New York flag previously had a field of buff, matching the color of troop uniforms. In 1901 it was changed to a field of blue to better follow the design of other military flags.
    .visual
      img(src='/assets/images/flag-new-york-pre-1901.svg')

